==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tam-tam
<hw>Tam"-tam`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.; of imitative
origin.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A kind of drum used
in the East Indies and other Oriental countries; -- called also
<altname>tom-tom</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A gong. See
<er>Gong</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tamul</ent>⟦br⟧
